```class Solution {
public:
    string minimizeStringValue(string s) {
        string res = "";
        char c = 'a';
        unordered_map<char, int> count;
        for (char ch : s) {
            if (ch != '?') {
                res += ch;
                count[ch]++;
            }
        }
        for (char ch : s) {
            if (ch == '?') {
                while (count.find(c) != count.end()) {
                    c++;
                }
                res += c;
                count[c]++;
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the string twice, first to count the occurrences of each character and then to replace the '?' characters with the smallest possible character that does not increase the cost.

